 items)\n8. Use contrast coding to code independent variables:\n- self-concept clarity (clear = +1, conflicted = −1)\n- rating distribution (bimodal = +1, unimodal = −1)\n9. Compute interaction term (Clarity × Rating Distribution).\n10. Run linear regression to predict desirability index through self-concept clarity, rating distribution and their interaction.\n11. Test the interaction effect of Self-concept clarity x Rating distribution on movie desirability index.",
